\b 1. Executive Summary\b0\par
This report covers the implementation and validation of Pantheon ULTRA mode after the earlier event-stream and audit work. The feature goal was to let one dialogue session temporarily escalate into a multi-expert synthesis flow with stable commands, safety checks, cached sessions, and deterministic behavior in stub mode.\par
\par
Delivered outcomes:\par
- canonical expert routing for architect and data-analyst style tasks;\par
- !ultra start and !normal stop commands;\par
- per-user Ultra session cache with follow-up continuity;\par
- deterministic synthesis and contradiction scoring;\par
- harmful-request refusal path in Ultra mode;\par
- regression and deep scenario coverage;\par
- final green validation gates.\par
\par
\b 2. Implemented Work\b0\par
The following implementation slices were completed.\par
\par
A. Ultra runtime orchestration\par
- Added command parsing for !ultra and !normal.\par
- Added session lifecycle helpers: create, refresh, prune, clear.\par
- Added follow-up reuse so additional user turns keep the same Ultra session id.\par
- Added report payloads under report.ultra for operator inspection.\par
\par
B. Expert router\par
